    "actor_description": "I can't get comfortable. My body keeps trying to do something-shift, check, adjust-like motion might keep the worry from landing. My thoughts don't sprint; they circle. The same few possibilities, each one sharpening a little as it comes around again. I notice my jaw set, my hands busy with nothing, my breath stuck high in my chest. Even when I tell myself it's fine, my nervous system doesn't believe me. I keep scanning for a problem I can fix, because the feeling itself won't sit still long enough to name.",
    "description_text": "{actor} can't settle-small movements constantly restarting: fingers worrying at a seam, foot tapping, weight shifting. Their gaze keeps flicking to corners and exits, then away again, as if attention won't hold. Breathing stays shallow, and they look busy without getting anywhere.",
